{
  "texts": [
    "The Shapelet Transform Classifier (STC) (Hills et al. 2014) is a pipeline classifier which searches the training data for shapelets, transforms series to vectors of s Dist distances to a filtered set of selected shapelets based on information gain, then builds a classifier on the latter.",
    "This is in contrast to the decision tree based approaches, which search for the best shapelet at each tree node.",
    "The first version of STC performed a full enumeration of all shapelets from all train cases before selecting the top k. 1.",
    "Search has been randomised, and the number of shapelets sampled is now a parameter, which defaults to 10,000.",
    "This does not lead to significantly worse performance on the UCR datasets. 2."
  ]
}